article.description: Pat Grace ran for two touchdowns and Terrell McMoore returned an interception 36 yards for what proved to be the decisive TD, giving Northern Iowa a 36-34 victory over New Hampshire on Saturday night in Championship Subdivision quarterfinals.
article.headline: Grace runs for two TDs as UNI gets by New Hampshire
article.linkText: McMoore's interception return propels N. Iowa
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa -- Pat Grace ran for two touchdowns and Terrell McMoore returned an interception 36 yards for what proved to be the decisive TD, giving Northern Iowa a 36-34 victory over New Hampshire on Saturday night in Championship Subdivision quarterfinals. The third-seeded Panthers (12-2) survived a 100-yard interception runback for a touchdown by New Hampshire's John Clements to move into next weekend's semifinals. They'll host Richmond on Friday night or Saturday afternoon. It was a typical playoff game between these two teams -- wild and close. Northern Iowa won 24-21 in 2005 and beat the Wildcats 38-35 on a last-second touchdown pass last year. New Hampshire's R.J. Toman was 16-of-30 passing for 243 yards and a touchdown, but he was intercepted four times and the Wildcats lost two fumbles. Grace went 18-for-26 for 255 yards and added 84 yards rushing on 14 carries.
